NOTICE
======

openshell-ext-authz — reference / demonstration code.

This repository is a runnable REFERENCE implementation of an external per-action
authorization egress middleware for OpenShell sandboxes, offered as an example
alongside Privacy Guard for the egress-middleware RFC (NVIDIA/OpenShell#1733).
It is licensed under Apache-2.0 (see LICENSE), matching OpenShell, so it can be
contributed to the RFC's examples/ as-is.

Scope — what this code is NOT:

* The demo verifier validates a deliberately simple HMAC-over-JSON token. This is
  NOT the real HAAP wire format; it exists only so the example is self-contained
  and dependency-free.
* Hawcx's production HAAP credential layer — designated-verifier Schnorr tokens,
  per-call proof-of-possession, enrolled agent identity, and revocation — is a
  SEPARATE, proprietary implementation and is NOT included in this repository.

HAAP (Hawcx Agent Auth Protocol) is patent pending.

